Get rows of a data.frame with identical values for the specified variables.

For hunting duplicate records during data cleaning. Specify the data.frame and the variable combination to search for duplicates and get back the duplicated rows.

get_dupes(dat, ...)

Arguments

dat

the input data.frame.
...

unquoted variable names to search for duplicates.

Value

Returns a data.frame (actually a tbl_df) with the full records where the specified variables have duplicated values, as well as a variable dupe_count showing the number of rows sharing that combination of duplicated values.

Examples

get_dupes(mtcars, mpg, hp)
#> # A tibble: 2 x 12
#>     mpg    hp dupe_count   cyl  disp  drat    wt  qsec    vs    am  gear  carb
#>   <dbl> <dbl>      <int> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl>
#> 1  21.0   110          2  6.00   160  3.90  2.62  16.5     0  1.00  4.00  4.00
#> 2  21.0   110          2  6.00   160  3.90  2.88  17.0     0  1.00  4.00  4.00
# or called with the magrittr pipe %>% :
mtcars %>% get_dupes(wt)
#> # A tibble: 5 x 12
#>      wt dupe_count   mpg   cyl  disp    hp  drat  qsec    vs    am  gear  carb
#>   <dbl>      <int> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl> <dbl>
#> 1  3.44          3  18.7  8.00   360   175  3.15  17.0  0     0     3.00  2.00
#> 2  3.44          3  19.2  6.00   168   123  3.92  18.3  1.00  0     4.00  4.00
#> 3  3.44          3  17.8  6.00   168   123  3.92  18.9  1.00  0     4.00  4.00
#> 4  3.57          2  14.3  8.00   360   245  3.21  15.8  0     0     3.00  4.00
#> 5  3.57          2  15.0  8.00   301   335  3.54  14.6  0     1.00  5.00  8.00
